query.prompt:
Please translate each line literally into English.

19 Io mi volsi dallato con paura
20 d’essere abbandonato, quand’ io vidi
21 solo dinanzi a me la terra oscura;

22 e ’l mio conforto: «Perché pur diffidi?»,
23 a dir mi cominciò tutto rivolto;
24 «non credi tu me teco e ch’io ti guidi?

25 Vespero è già colà dov’ è sepolto
26 lo corpo dentro al quale io facea ombra;
27 Napoli l’ha, e da Brandizio è tolto.

query.result:
19 I turned to the side with fear
20 of being abandoned, when I saw
21 only before me the dark earth;

22 and my comfort: “Why do you still distrust?”
23 began to speak to me, completely turned towards me;
24 “Do you not believe I am with you and that I guide you?

25 Evening is already there where is buried
26 the body within which I made shade;
27 Naples has it, and it is taken from Brandizio.”

37 Be content, human people, with “because”; 38 because, if you had been able to see everything, 39 it would not have been necessary for Mary to give birth;
40 and you would have desired without fruit 41 those whose desire would be quieted, 42 that eternally is given to them for sorrow:
43 I speak of Aristotle and of Plato 44 and of many others”; and here he lowered his forehead, 45 and said no more, and remained troubled.

46 We meanwhile came to the foot of the mountain;
47 there we found the rock so steep,
48 that in vain would be ready legs.

64 He looked then, and with free bearing
65 responded: “Let us go there, for they come slowly;
66 and you hold back your hope, sweet son.”

