Please translate each line literally into English.
79 Come le pecorelle escon del chiuso 80 a una, a due, a tre, e l’altre stanno 81 timidette atterrando l’occhio e ’l muso;
82 e ciò che fa la prima, e l’altre fanno, 83 addossandosi a lei, s’ella s’arresta, 84 semplici e quete, e lo ’mperché non sanno;
85 sì vid’ io muovere a venir la testa 86 di quella mandra fortunata allotta, 87 pudica in faccia e ne l’andare onesta.

query.result:
79 As the little sheep come out of the enclosure 80 one by one, two by two, three by three, and the others stay 81 timidly lowering the eye and the snout;
82 and what the first one does, the others do, 83 leaning towards her, if she stops, 84 simple and quiet, and they do not know why;
85 thus I saw moving to come the head 86 of that fortunate flock all at once, 87 modest in face and honest in the walking.

94 Without your asking, I confess to you
95 that this is a human body that you see;
96 for the light of the sun is bent on earth.

109 When I humbly excused myself
110 for ever having seen him, he said: “Now see”;
111 and he showed me a wound on the very top of the chest.

121 Horrible were my sins;
122 but the infinite goodness has such great arms,
123 that it takes what turns to it.

